      <h1 class='title'>Container Security</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 09 December 2002 vol 396 c1WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1ws' title='Col. 1WS &mdash; HC Deb 09 December 2002 vol 396 c1WS' name='column_1ws' href='#column_1ws' rel='bookmark'>1WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0396P0_20021209_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-gordon-brown' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0396P0_20021209_CWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Mr Gordon Brown' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-gordon-brown" title="Mr Gordon Brown">The Chancellor of the Exchequer (Mr. Gordon Brown)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Her Majesty's Customs and Excise and the United States Customs Service signed a Declaration of Principles to implement the Container Security Initiative today, 9 December. Detailed guidance on how the Initiative will be implemented and on deployment of US Customs Officers at UK ports will be agreed in the New Year. A copy of the Declaration has been placed in the Library.</p><p><table>
